  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "Хоте́ть in full, and но vs а",
    "explanation": "**Хоте́ть** (to want) is irregular — it switches conjugation halfway through: **хочу́, хо́чешь, хо́чет** (like a 1st-conjugation verb) but **хоти́м, хоти́те, хотя́т** (like a 2nd-conjugation verb). You already know хочу́ from Day 1 — now you have the whole set.\n\nYou know **и** (and, simple addition) and **а** (and/but, a soft contrast — \"I do X, and you do Y\"). **Но** is a *stronger* but — a real contradiction: **Я хочу́ чита́ть, но э́то тру́дно** — I want to read, but it's difficult.",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "Мы хоти́м гуля́ть.", "en": "We want to walk.", "note": "хотим — 2nd-conj-style ending" },
      { "ru": "Вы хоти́те чай?", "en": "Do you (formal) want tea?" },
      { "ru": "Я чита́ю, а ты слу́шаешь.", "en": "I'm reading, and you're listening.", "note": "а — soft contrast" },
      { "ru": "Я хочу́ чита́ть, но э́то тру́дно.", "en": "I want to read, but it's difficult.", "note": "но — real contradiction" }
    ]
  },

